1
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:04,740
(Episode 33)

2
00:00:04,740 --> 00:00:09,010
I need to get him to talk
about Kang Jun Ho naturally.

3
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:10,920
How do I do this?

4
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:14,690
This wine is especially fragrant today.

5
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:16,590
I saw you...

6
00:00:17,190 --> 00:00:19,920
meeting with Chef Kang Jun Ho earlier.

7
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:27,800
If I'd known he was your son,
I wouldn't have been so harsh.

8
00:00:29,770 --> 00:00:31,470
No, it's all right.

9
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,110
If he did something to displease you,

10
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:38,580
then my son is the one at fault.

11
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:42,250
Not at all.
Really, I feel terrible about it.

12
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,350
But...

13
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:48,790
Chef Kang doesn't resemble you at all.

14
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:51,820
To be honest,

15
00:00:52,020 --> 00:00:56,130
I'm not sure
if I should be telling you this,

16
00:00:57,100 --> 00:01:00,270
but I feel like you might have
the wrong idea about Jun Ho.

17
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:03,840
So, in the hopes that you'll understand,

18
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,770
I'd like to share something personal.

19
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,210
The truth is, Jun Ho...

20
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:15,410
is adopted.

21
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:19,620
I see.

22
00:01:20,020 --> 00:01:24,190
You know the saying that some children
are born from the heart?

23
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:27,390
That's how it was with Jun Ho.

24
00:01:28,790 --> 00:01:32,100
He had been returned to the orphanage
after being diagnosed with leukemia.

25
00:01:33,770 --> 00:01:36,000
We saw him sitting in a corner
of the orphanage playground,

26
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:39,740
watching the other kids run and play.

27
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:42,770
I could just see the longing in his eyes.

28
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:47,010
When I saw him like that,

29
00:01:48,250 --> 00:01:51,950
my heart just ached for him.

30
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:57,360
My wife told me she felt
the exact same way.

31
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:01,060
And that's how he became our son,
born in our hearts.

32
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:04,300
Thank you.

33
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:08,130
I'm sorry?

34
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,070
I'm thanking you for doing
such a wonderful thing, Professor.

35
00:02:16,610 --> 00:02:19,010
I'm honestly so touched.

36
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,350
I don't deserve such praise.

37
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:28,820
The orphanage couldn't afford
to treat his leukemia,

38
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:30,460
and without treatment,

39
00:02:31,390 --> 00:02:33,190
the poor child's life was at risk.

40
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:37,400
My wife and I simply did
what had to be done.

41
00:02:58,750 --> 00:02:59,880
Are you crying?

42
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,220
I'm just so moved.

43
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:09,260
To help a child who was
a complete stranger like that...

44
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:14,130
Jun Ho was so lucky
to have met you and your wife.

45
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:15,870
Jun Ho...

46
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:20,070
may seem cold on the outside,
but he's actually very tenderhearted.

47
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:23,210
He fought a terrible illness as a child...

48
00:03:24,740 --> 00:03:26,710
and carries the scars of being abandoned.

49
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,750
He's a child who's overcome so much,

50
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,280
so please, try to understand him.

51
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:34,850
I'm so sorry.

52
00:03:35,390 --> 00:03:39,190
So that's what made him so guarded.
I completely misjudged him.

53
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:43,700
I had no idea your son was raised
by such wonderful parents.

54
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:46,600
Don't you worry.

55
00:03:47,370 --> 00:03:49,130
I'll make up for my misjudgment...

56
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,340
and be extra good
to Chef Kang from now on.

57
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,610
(Wife)

58
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,480
Go on, answer it.

59
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,120
Excuse me.

60
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,420
(Wife)

61
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:10,560
Honey.

62
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:13,790
You said you were going out for some air.
Where are you? You're still not home.

63
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:17,000
The Dream Hotel called me.

64
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:24,240
The project is about to kick off,
so there were some details to iron out.

65
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:29,510
I swear, people just won't let
a hardworking man like you get any rest.

66
00:04:30,340 --> 00:04:33,010
- Be careful not to catch a cold.
- I will. Don't worry.

67
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:36,110
I got to eat great food,

68
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:38,820
and I got to wear this beautiful outfit,

69
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:41,290
but don't ever ask me
to play a role like that again.

70
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:42,450
Why not?

71
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,760
You were a total natural at this.

72
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:45,890
Excuse me?

73
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:49,130
You're not really going to keep asking me
to be your fake girlfriend, are you?

74
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,660
Of course not. Absolutely not.

75
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:57,400
Then I'll go and return this outfit.
Wait here for a second.

76
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,120
Let's date for real.

77
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:23,560
No more pretending.

78
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:27,100
Please, be my woman.

79
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,440
I...

80
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:36,110
want to be your man, Jang Mi.

81
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,010
I have...

82
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,880
genuine feelings for you.

83
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,540
Oh, hey, Tae Sook.

84
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:06,140
Jang Mi, when are you getting home?

85
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,570
Mom is freaking out, looking for you.

86
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:11,740
- Mom is?
- Yes, so get here, quick.

87
00:06:12,110 --> 00:06:13,540
All right.

88
00:06:19,950 --> 00:06:22,750
You don't have to answer me right now.

89
00:06:25,990 --> 00:06:28,360
Thank you for dinner. Get home safely.

90
00:06:53,850 --> 00:06:56,350
Baek Ho, I'm sorry.

91
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,490
Liking someone is a luxury I can't afford.

92
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:02,460
I have to be there for my mom.

93
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,530
Mom, I'm home!

94
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:09,130
It's me, Mom.
Your daughter, Jang Mi, is home.

95
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:16,740
Professor Kang.

96
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,880
I'm sorry if I made you uncomfortable.

97
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:23,150
No, that's not it. It's just...

98
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,920
After hearing what you said,

99
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,850
it sounds like your wife
is a wonderful person.

100
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:31,920
So I don't think it's right
for us to keep meeting like this.

101
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:34,690
What are you talking about?

102
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:37,130
We're doing your wife a great wrong.

103
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:40,030
I don't want to be the cause of her pain.

104
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,070
Hwa Young.

105
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:46,100
You're not saying
you won't see me again, are you?

106
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,270
It's just given me a lot to think about.

107
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:51,710
Don't do this.

108
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:54,750
You're just feeling sorry for my wife,
but what about me?

109
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:58,620
Haven't you thought about
how hurt I'd be if I lost you?

110
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,650
I shouldn't have mentioned Jun Ho.

111
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:06,190
I've always known you had a good heart,

112
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:09,630
but I never realized
you were this soft-hearted.

113
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:13,500
- It just feels morally wrong.
- Hwa Young.

114
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,570
Anyway, it's getting late,

115
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:17,440
so I'm going to head out for today.

116
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,770
No, wait, Hwa Young.

117
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:20,970
Hwa Young!

118
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:23,140
I didn't hear a word you said!

119
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:26,140
I'll call you, Hwa Young! Okay?

120
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:28,710
There you go.

121
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:34,450
Don't worry, I won't ever leave you.

122
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:36,050
Jang Mi is so pretty.

123
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,220
Suk Hee was looking for Jang Mi.

124
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,520
When Jang Mi's not here,

125
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:42,260
Suk Hee gets scared.

126
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:46,000
- I told you not to worry.
- Suk Hee.

127
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:49,730
Jang Mi is all grown up.
She needs to date and have a life,

128
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,700
but she can't live her life
if you're always holding her back.

129
00:08:54,770 --> 00:08:56,140
Jang Mi is so pretty.

130
00:08:56,810 --> 00:09:00,710
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.
Jang Mi is so pretty.

131
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,610
Of course.

132
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:13,690
Chairman.

133
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,760
CEO Chae is just coming in.

134
00:09:16,730 --> 00:09:18,230
All right.

135
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,070
CEO Chae should really get an earful now.

136
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:25,700
A daughter-in-law
sneaking around with some man?

137
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,940
How shameful.

138
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:37,880
I'm home, Father.

139
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:39,520
You're late.

140
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,620
- Yes.
- You must be tired.

141
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:46,090
- Go and get some rest.
- I will. Good night.

142
00:10:10,950 --> 00:10:11,950
Ha Neul.

143
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:15,920
Could it really be you, my son Ha Neul?

144
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,220
I moved to the US when I was 20,

145
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:20,830
and after working abroad for so long,

146
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:24,760
I felt it was time to come back to Korea,
where my parents live.

147
00:10:25,430 --> 00:10:26,500
More than anything,

148
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:28,370
I've always dreamed of
combining Western and Korean cuisine...

149
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:31,970
to pioneer my own unique culinary style.

150
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:36,470
If Kang Jun Ho really is Ha Neul...

151
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,980
I can't believe he grew up so well.

152
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,350
After I abandoned you,

153
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:48,320
and as if that wasn't enough,
I was so cruel to you.

154
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:50,290
What am I going to do?

155
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:55,590
I'm so sorry, Jun Ho.

156
00:10:57,030 --> 00:10:59,760
How could I ever face you
and call myself your mother?

157
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:06,700
No.

158
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:10,240
I have to be absolutely sure.

159
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,080
Seriously?

160
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:16,480
You even showed the Chairman
a picture of them together,

161
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,450
and that was his reaction?

162
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:22,150
I have no idea
what the Chairman is thinking.

163
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,490
You don't think he's just going to
let her off the hook, do you?

164
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:26,820
That's ridiculous.

165
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:31,000
Even if the Chairman does nothing,
I won't let her get away with it.

166
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:34,600
I refuse to stand by and watch
Chae Hwa Young have an affair.

167
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:37,000
Well, technically, it's not an affair.

168
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,240
She's been single for a long time.

169
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:42,740
- Her husband died ages ago.
- Be quiet!

170
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:46,180
Don't you know we have to get
Seo Rin and Hwa Young out of here...

171
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,280
if we want to take over Dream?

172
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,650
Find out who that guy is discreetly.

173
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:58,690
Yes, Chairman.

174
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:07,060
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

175
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:15,410
I have...

176
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,240
genuine feelings for you.

177
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:34,690
No, that's impossible.
There's no way Baek Ho has a girlfriend.

178
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,800
What?

179
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:41,200
He brought his girlfriend
to the blind date?

180
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:53,340
Anyway,

181
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:56,580
leave it to my son,
Kang Baek Ho, to embarrass me.

182
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:59,320
Mom, I told you exactly how I felt.

183
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,920
But you're the one who completely
ignored me and went ahead anyway.

184
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:04,720
I can't believe this. Watch how you talk!

185
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:06,890
If that's how you felt,
you should've just refused to go.

186
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:09,430
Why did you have to bring
that Jang Mi girl...

187
00:13:09,430 --> 00:13:10,460
and cause such a scene?

188
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,000
It wasn't a scene.

189
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:16,000
Baek Ho. Did you really take
Oh Jang Mi to your blind date?

190
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:19,570
- Even after I warned you?
- Why is everyone ganging up on me?

191
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,370
Why are you so against her
when you haven't even met her?

192
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:25,310
Fine. In that case,
bring her home sometime.

193
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:28,680
If she's so great, introduce her
to the family, and then you can date her.

194
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:32,150
Better yet, bring her to the restaurant.
Let me meet her first.

195
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:33,780
Will you?

196
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:41,660
Hi, Jang Mi.

197
00:13:42,130 --> 00:13:43,130
Goodness.

198
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:49,870
Jang Mi, did you sleep well?

199
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:52,140
How are you feeling? Have you eaten?

200
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,640
One question at a time.

201
00:13:54,940 --> 00:13:56,910
Didn't you miss me?

202
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,810
There's something I need to tell you.

203
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:02,380
Let's meet up later.

204
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:10,850
I need to know for sure if Kang Jun Ho...

205
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:13,520
is really Ha Neul.

206
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,090
I can't be sure
based on circumstances alone.

207
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:21,430
Come in.

208
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:31,310
I need to be sure...

209
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,340
that you're really my son.

210
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:36,950
Come on in.

211
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:38,580
Have a seat.

212
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,890
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

213
00:14:47,090 --> 00:14:48,530
What's all this about?

214
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,330
I'm sorry,

215
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:54,970
but I have no intention of quitting.

216
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:58,500
It looks like you're trying to find
some excuse to fire me,

217
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:01,440
which is why you've arranged
this ridiculous meeting.

218
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:04,310
If that's what you're hoping for,
you can forget it.

219
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:08,280
And why is it that you can't quit?

220
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:10,750
Let's hear your reason.

221
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,950
I don't know
if you remember what I said...

222
00:15:13,550 --> 00:15:15,590
when I first started here,

223
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,890
but Chang Restaurant was a complete mess.

224
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,790
The reason I turned down offers
from other places to come here...

225
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:26,960
was that I had a plan to turn
this mess into a top-tier restaurant.

226
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,730
Working at a top restaurant
that's already at the top is no fun.

227
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,110
I see.

228
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:39,680
I completely understand
where you're coming from,

229
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:41,550
so there's no need to be so defensive.

230
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:47,520
Actually, the reason
I asked you here today...

231
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:50,620
is that I wanted to make amends with you.

232
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,930
- Make amends?
- Yes.

233
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:57,460
After giving it a lot of thought,

234
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:01,730
I realize that as your superior,
I've been terrible to you.

235
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:05,740
I was being petty
just because you were scouted...

236
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:06,900
by Team Leader Jin Hong Ju.

237
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,370
I'm sorry.

238
00:16:09,370 --> 00:16:10,570
I apologize.

239
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:19,820
I'm not interested in making peace.

240
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:24,660
Because an employee and their boss
can't really have a fight.

241
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,390
You've got a point there.

242
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:30,090
Thank you.

243
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,530
Please, have some.

244
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,310
I'm admitting I was terrible to you.

245
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:43,770
Aren't you going to accept my apology?

246
00:16:45,910 --> 00:16:48,550
I went out of my way to get this
from a popular cake shop.

247
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:50,610
Try some...

248
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:55,650
and see how it compares
to our own pastry chef's work.

249
00:16:57,220 --> 00:16:58,290
So that's what this was about.

250
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:02,330
Looks like you've changed
your strategy to a charm offensive.

251
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:21,750
It's a bit sweet, but it's good.

252
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:24,480
Satisfied?

253
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:30,550
I have customers with a reservation.

254
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:32,820
I should be going now.

255
00:17:37,930 --> 00:17:40,030
This little show
only needs to happen once.

256
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,800
- Don't call me out like this again.
- That's...

257
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:47,200
not your decision to make, Chef Kang.
It's mine.

258
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:50,570
In a few days,
I'll book us a table for dinner...

259
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,310
at a more relaxed setting.

260
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:12,030
(Kang Jun Ho)

261
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:24,010
(Kang Jun Ho, Chae Hwa Young)

262
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:27,980
(Kang Jun Ho)

263
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,820
That's amazing.

264
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:45,630
Your plating is a true work of art.

265
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,370
Could you leave?
You're getting on my nerves.

266
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:59,480
You handle those plates so gently,
like they're babies.

267
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:04,550
Oh, right.
I'll make some beautiful pottery...

268
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:05,850
and give it to you as a gift.

269
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:09,720
Then, on the plates I made for you,
you can make me something delicious.

270
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:11,990
Deal?

271
00:19:21,570 --> 00:19:24,300
Jang Mi, if you're going to see
Lawyer Kang, give this to him.

272
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:27,740
Dad, Lawyer Kang didn't
even order a lunch box.

273
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:28,810
Why should I take it to him?

274
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:31,010
He loves our lunch boxes.

275
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:34,380
I just made it, but if he's eaten,
he can have it for dinner.

276
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:35,580
Just take it to him.

277
00:19:35,710 --> 00:19:38,020
- But...
- Just do what I tell you.

278
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:39,780
When someone does you a favor,

279
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:41,950
you have to pay them back,
even in small ways. Got it?

280
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:45,120
Okay, I'll be back.

281
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:47,960
Hey, Oh Jang Mi.

282
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:49,860
You know Lawyer Kang
has a crush on you, right?

283
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:53,730
He's kind, handsome,
and he's head over heels for you.

284
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,170
It's not easy to find a guy like that.

285
00:19:55,370 --> 00:19:57,940
Shut up. Don't you start, too.

286
00:19:57,940 --> 00:19:59,200
You have no idea how I really feel.

287
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:05,910
She said you don't know how she feels.
What's that supposed to mean?

288
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,280
Good.

289
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:15,520
How may I help you?

290
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:18,520
So this was how it looked.

291
00:20:19,290 --> 00:20:20,760
Are you here to take a pottery class?

292
00:20:21,530 --> 00:20:23,090
Why else would I be here?

293
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:27,660
We have classes twice a week,
on Mondays and Wednesdays.

294
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:29,530
- The monthly fee is...
- Whatever.

295
00:20:30,130 --> 00:20:31,640
When can I start?

296
00:20:33,470 --> 00:20:36,810
- Not with those nails, you can't.
- My nails?

297
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:39,710
What's wrong with them?
I think they're beautiful.

298
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:43,350
I paid good money for these.

299
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,650
There are some rules
if you want to take a class here.

300
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:50,890
- Rules?
- First of all, you need to dress...

301
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:54,730
more appropriately
and cut your nails short.

302
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:57,330
To work with clay,
your nails have to be clean and short.

303
00:20:58,130 --> 00:21:02,030
My love for Jun Ho is making me
sacrifice even my precious nails.

304
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:03,270
Excuse me?

305
00:21:06,670 --> 00:21:08,170
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

306
00:21:08,810 --> 00:21:09,970
Here.

307
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:12,480
I think it's best if I return this.

308
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:16,450
Come on. You expect me to wear this dress?

309
00:21:16,610 --> 00:21:17,780
And the earrings too?

310
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:22,420
That's up to you.
Anyway, I can't accept these.

311
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,990
- Jang Mi.
- I have something to say.

312
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:29,190
Hold on. What's the big rush?

313
00:21:31,630 --> 00:21:33,200
I was really looking forward
to having your lunch box.

314
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:35,600
- Thanks.
- Baek Ho.

315
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,440
I mean, Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

316
00:21:40,470 --> 00:21:41,770
Please don't have feelings for me.

317
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:46,210
You said you wanted to be my man, right?

318
00:21:46,210 --> 00:21:47,310
But...

319
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:49,510
I can't let that happen.

320
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:53,020
Is this your answer...

321
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:54,620
to my question?

322
00:21:54,620 --> 00:21:55,850
I'm sorry,

323
00:21:57,090 --> 00:21:58,160
but, yes.

324
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,000
Come out.

325
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:16,010
Why?

326
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:18,110
I want to know why.

327
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,010
Don't I have the right to like you?

328
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:25,320
I'm the one who isn't good enough.

329
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,880
Besides,

330
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:30,250
you know what my situation is like.

331
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,290
Being in a relationship...

332
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:36,190
is for people who have
the time and emotional space for it.

333
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:39,360
And I just don't.

334
00:22:41,230 --> 00:22:42,800
And I'm not the right person...

335
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:45,740
for someone like you anyway.

336
00:22:46,170 --> 00:22:47,970
Who decides who's worthy of whom?

337
00:22:49,210 --> 00:22:51,840
Everyone has the freedom
to be with whom they choose.

338
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:54,950
And that freedom itself is
all the qualification you need.

339
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:56,850
Baek Ho.

340
00:22:56,850 --> 00:22:59,980
Do you think I'm crazy to just hang around
a woman I don't even like...

341
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:02,420
and bend over backwards
to help out her family?

342
00:23:04,290 --> 00:23:06,620
I like you, Jang Mi.

343
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:07,620
I mean...

344
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:08,730
I love you.

345
00:23:09,830 --> 00:23:11,660
I told you before.
Do you really think I'm kidding?

346
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,160
Baek Ho...

347
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,840
At first, I thought I just liked you.

348
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:21,770
But...

349
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,210
when I almost lost you,
I realized something.

350
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,250
I realized I was in love with this woman.

351
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:31,280
And that's why...

352
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,820
I can never let you go.

353
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,290
Can't you see how sincere I am?

354
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,160
Love is a luxury I can't afford.

355
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:48,470
My mom needs me.

356
00:23:49,270 --> 00:23:51,670
Who said anything about
taking you away from your mother?

357
00:23:52,740 --> 00:23:55,110
What does our loving each other
have to do with your mother?

358
00:23:55,170 --> 00:23:56,610
We can absolutely make it work.

359
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:59,410
So stop running away and stop hesitating.

360
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,380
Just tell me.

361
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:04,820
You have feelings for me too.

362
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:06,620
Don't you?

363
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:09,450
Just be honest with yourself.

364
00:24:15,690 --> 00:24:16,760
I'll wait.

365
00:24:18,630 --> 00:24:21,600
If you still have feelings
for Chef Kang Jun Ho,

366
00:24:22,570 --> 00:24:24,900
I can wait until you come to like me.

367
00:24:25,140 --> 00:24:26,200
No.

368
00:24:26,940 --> 00:24:28,040
Don't wait for me.

369
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:31,510
I'm telling you not to wait for me.

370
00:24:32,010 --> 00:24:34,110
I already told you.
I don't do things like fall in love.

371
00:24:35,650 --> 00:24:37,310
So it's no use waiting for me.

372
00:24:39,450 --> 00:24:40,520
Jang Mi.

373
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:00,100
I don't want to...

374
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,940
make you carry my burdens too.

375
00:25:04,410 --> 00:25:06,380
You've done more than enough
for me already.

376
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:15,890
(Law Firm Leeho)

377
00:25:18,690 --> 00:25:20,260
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

378
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:28,100
What does he see in the girl who works
at the side dish shop...

379
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:30,100
that makes him so crazy about her?

380
00:25:30,100 --> 00:25:31,270
Good grief.

381
00:25:31,740 --> 00:25:33,500
The girl who works at the side dish shop?

382
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:36,310
Oh, my.

383
00:25:37,540 --> 00:25:40,810
Hello. I did knock before I came in.

384
00:25:41,850 --> 00:25:43,950
I'm so sorry,
I didn't realize I had a visitor.

385
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:48,050
Goodness.
The whole office must smell like food.

386
00:25:48,850 --> 00:25:50,120
I'm so sorry about that.

387
00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:51,620
Please, have a seat.

388
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:55,730
That's all right. I'm here to consult
with Lawyer Kang Baek Ho,

389
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:57,860
but I guess he's not here?

390
00:25:57,930 --> 00:25:59,200
May I ask what it's about?

391
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,130
I work with him, so you can just tell me.

392
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:03,470
The thing is,

393
00:26:03,970 --> 00:26:05,840
I'm here to see Baek Ho.

394
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:15,550
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

395
00:26:15,610 --> 00:26:18,150
What does he see in the girl who works
at the side dish shop...

396
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:20,150
that makes him so crazy about her?

397
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:21,250
Good grief.

398
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:22,850
So Lawyer Kang Baek Ho...

399
00:26:23,150 --> 00:26:25,320
is dating a woman
who works at a side dish shop?

400
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:40,840
Welcome.

401
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:47,480
No way.
Lawyer Kang is dating a woman like her?

402
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:49,950
This can't be right.

403
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:51,280
Have a look around.

404
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:53,080
The seasoned vegetables
are three for ten dollars,

405
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:54,320
but I'll throw in an extra one for you.

406
00:26:54,850 --> 00:26:56,490
We also take orders for lunch boxes.

407
00:26:58,360 --> 00:26:59,360
Okay.

408
00:27:06,830 --> 00:27:10,170
I wonder if Lawyer Kang Baek Ho
enjoyed his lunch box.

409
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:13,340
Lawyer Kang loves our lunch boxes,
you know?

410
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:17,070
He's one of a kind.
A truly genuine person.

411
00:27:17,210 --> 00:27:19,480
He always bends over backwards
to help our family.

412
00:27:19,810 --> 00:27:23,350
He does all that
because he has feelings, right?

413
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:24,910
Tell me something I don't know.

414
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:28,750
Gosh, so it is true.

415
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:32,260
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho is into that woman.

416
00:27:33,060 --> 00:27:34,090
Unbelievable.

417
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:37,560
Right.

418
00:27:37,860 --> 00:27:40,900
So who on earth is this guy
that CEO Chae is dating?

419
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:43,870
Kang Nam Bong. He's a professor
in the Industrial Design Department,

420
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:47,000
and he joined
our hotel's renovation project.

421
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:49,970
(Profile: Kang Nam Bong)

422
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:52,480
So that's how they met.

423
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,640
And I believe...

424
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:56,350
he's participating in
the Dream Resort project.

425
00:28:11,830 --> 00:28:13,960
The Chairman wants you in his study.

426
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,370
What's this about?

427
00:28:17,570 --> 00:28:20,700
What have you been up to every night?

428
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:22,170
Pardon?

429
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:32,420
I'm asking what you've been doing
with a married man.

430
00:28:57,010 --> 00:28:58,440
(The First Man)

431
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:01,440
So they sent the DNA results by courier?

432
00:29:03,050 --> 00:29:05,050
Did I intrude?

433
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:08,320
Is there someone here named Oh Jang Mi?

434
00:29:08,420 --> 00:29:11,220
You seem busy,
so I'll get straight to the point.

435
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:16,260
If I'm going to be this crazy,
I might as well just ask Baek Ho out.

436
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:19,260
I saw you crying earlier,
looking at Kang Jun Ho tenderly.

437
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:21,300
You're hiding something from me,
aren't you?

438
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,800
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
